Meet Devon Layne, a dynamic young African American entrepreneur with a passion for making life easier for people. Born to parents from Barbados, he grew up in the inner city of Boston, Massachusetts, where he developed a keen interest in business from a young age. After attending Suffolk University for business, he decided to drop out and gain hands-on experience in the business world.

Starting as a used car dealer, Devon quickly gained a reputation for his sharp eye and savvy business sense. With the profits from flipping cars, he founded Pick a Layne, a rental car service that provided a much-needed service to travelers and locals alike.

Through hard work, dedication, and a deep understanding of his customers' needs, Devon has become a trusted name in the business world. With a bright future ahead of him, he's poised to make an even greater impact on the world of business and beyond.

Hello Folks, my name is Sam, and welcome to Turo!
I have a growing Turo fleet with a focus on providing affordable, reliable, and economical cars for anyone who needs a vehicle.

All of my cars have instant booking turned ON, and all of them are remote key exchange - meaning I won't actually be there when you pick up the vehicle. This gives you a more convenient and flexible booking and rental experience. 

My cars aren't perfect, they all have minor wear and tear, so if you are looking for a perfect rental car that is in showroom floor quality then unfortunately my cars are not for you. But, if you are looking for a professionally maintained, reliable, and clean car then my car fleet is perfect for you.

Though all of my cars have wear and tear they are all meticulously maintained, they are all cleaned and disinfected between every single rental and they will all get you to where you need to go at an affordable price. 

If you are looking for a host you can count on, then look no further than my fleet of vehicles.
